A police constable in the North West who was filmed drunk on duty has been dismissed. His dismissal follows an internal disciplinary process into the incident, which occurred on Saturday, November 28, said Brig Sabata Mokgwabone. A video depicted the fully-uniformed and intoxicated cop struggling to stand on his feet to inspect damages on a state motor vehicle after he had reversed  into a fence in Wolmaransstad. He is facing charges of driving under the influence of alcohol and  using a motor vehicle without the owner's consent. He is due to appear in court on March 19. TimesLIVE